      "hypothesis": "In BULL_STRESSED, upward CUSUM breaks (cumulative move exceeding 1.0 ATR) mark absorption-then-continuation: elevated realized vol with LOW volume (0.468) means moves are liquidity-thin repricings, not distribution, so a confirmed 1-ATR upside impulse continues on the LONG side. Falling real yields (0.382) and falling breakevens (0.437) supply an exogenous discount-rate tailwind that discriminates which breaks pay.",
      "causal_story": "Reachability: cusum at threshold_atr 2.0 gave ~19,659 pooled ungated events (35 names); counts scale several-fold as threshold falls, so at 1.0 expect ~40,000-60,000 ungated. The 7% BULL_STRESSED gate leaves ~2,800-4,200 events, 4-7x above the 599 raw and 799 effective-N floors. Mechanism: high rv_20 with BELOW-median volume (0.468) is thin-liquidity repricing - a 1-ATR cumulative impulse reflects genuine demand imbalance, not crowd exhaustion. Meta uses within-regime real_yield_5y_z252d (IQR 0.19-0.87) and cs_spread_21 (IQR 0.40-0.85): ungated AUC was flat (0.531) because the effect is vol-conditional. Side LONG with regime drift; no claim rests on the n=25 bollinger hit rate.",
      "feature_overrides": {
        "add": [
          "real_yield_5y_z252d",
          "cs_spread_21",
          "volume",
          "breakeven_5y_chg5",
          "vix_chg_5"
        ],
        "drop": []
